## Two architecture questions answered (text-only, no tools)

Before the slice 1b plan-first, two design questions were resolved:

**Q1 — Render worker location:**
Correct approach: `Dockerfile.render` pointing at `apps/api/` source, different CMD.
No new workspace package. No standalone entry point existed — `main.ts` boots the
full `AppModule`. Two new files needed:
- `apps/api/src/render-worker.module.ts` — slim module with `WorkerHealthController`
  (needed for Fly scale-to-zero HTTP detection) + `ReportCardRenderModule` import chain
- `apps/api/src/main-render-worker.ts` — `NestFactory.create()` (not
  `createApplicationContext()`) so an HTTP listener exists for Fly; `enableShutdownHooks()`
  for SIGTERM drain on scale-to-zero
BullMQ `@Processor` hooks into NestJS module lifecycle, not the HTTP adapter; works
correctly with `NestFactory.create()`.

**Q2 — cp3 sequencing:**
Fold into slice 1b cp1 (not a separate commit on the docs branch). Stripping
Chromium from the API and creating the render worker Dockerfile are one coherent
Tier 2 change. Splitting them produces a broken intermediate state (API has no
Chrome, render worker doesn't exist yet). Image size is only a push-to-Fly problem;
nothing is deployed until slice 1b anyway.

